message.content: N/a. The authors do not explicitly include the total amount of compute and the type of resources used for their experiments. However, they do mention that all models are trained on 1 NVIDIA TITAN RTX GPU and provide the longest training time (for the expert PARKING agent) as roughly 5 hours.

No, the authors do not explicitly mention the total amount of compute used in their experiments. They do mention the use of 1 NVIDIA TITAN RTX GPU for training their models, but they do not provide information about the total compute time or any details regarding cloud providers or internal clusters.

Yes, the authors mention the type of GPU used for their experiments in Appendix I - "All models are trained on 1 NVIDIA TITAN RTX GPU." However, they do not provide explicit information about whether they used an internal cluster or a cloud provider.
